In `doc/types/README.md`, list all data types and note which ones are considered
'basic' and 'composite'. Composite data types are basically all collections +
all user-defined data types -- they are supposed to begin with a Capital Letter.

Record source code, assembly, and bytecode standards to provide grounds for
coherent implementation.

Finalize Scoops Source Code, Assembly, and Virtual Machine designs to be able to
implement them and exhaust resources inside the `.old` folder. It has to be
removed soon after.
